]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[The aim of the programme is to explore and study the social and cultural dimensions of human sexuality and gain training in areas of sexuality research - both theory and method - not commonly available in other institutions. Sexuality is studied from a broader perspective in order to understand safe or risky behaviour regarding HIV infection. In other words, the study of the relation between sexuality and HIV/AIDS should focus on the way how social axes like gender, age and ethnicity, or ideas o]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>socio-economic contribution</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Participants are encouraged to critically analyse documented examples of 'good practice' in the field and examine the underlying assumptions. They also explore how theoretical approaches to sexuality are and can be incorporated in organizing at the grassroots and community levels, within media efforts, and at the policy level. The sharing of varied experiences, research, plans of work and perspectives provide a unique networking opportunity, thereby increasing participants’ knowledge within an]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>sustainable strengthening</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Application consists of: 

